@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "DeerPost Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>Privacy policy</h1>

<p>This policy describes how DeerPost.cx stores and processes your data when you use this website. DeerPost.cx is a independent initiative run within EMF. This policy was last updated on the 29th June 2026.</p>

<p>We will never sell your data to anyone, and we will never share it with any other organisation except as detailed below. Unless specifically mentioned in this policy, all attendee data held by us will be deleted no later than 12 months after the end of the event it relates to.</p>

<h2>What we collect</h2>
<p>To run the website, we ask for information that you provide yourself: your username, your pronouns, a profile, an avatar selected from a list we provide, and your physical address within the event. We require the physical address in the event to send you postcards, other information is optional. When you send or register a sent postcard, we store the date and time when the postcard was registered.</p>

<p>You can optionally provide your email. It is only used for account-related messages such as notifications and password resets. Your email is never disclosed to others. If you do not want to receive emails, just don't provide it.</p>

<h2>Why we need it</h2>
<p>This information is only used to make the website work — things like displaying your profile, sending and registering postcards, and displaying the postcard information. We don't use this information for marketing or anything outside the event.</p>

<h2>Who can see it</h2>
<p>DeerPost.cx is only accessible within EMF's network. On the public Internet, only a simple landing page is displayed and you cannot log into the website from it. The website information not shared with any third parties, sponsors, or external services. Only the caretaker, who runs the website, has access to the data.</p>

<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>We use cookies solely to keep you logged in. We don't use tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or any other kind of cookie beyond what's needed to maintain your session.</p>

<h2>Internet privacy</h2>
<p>We take the privacy and anonymity of our users very seriously. We actively avoid logging all unnecessary data.</p>

<h2>Web request logs and analytics</h2>
<p>Like most websites, our server automatically logs basic information about each request, including IP addresses. We do this for two reasons only: troubleshooting technical issues and dealing with abuse. These logs are not used for any other purpose, and we keep them for as short a time as possible — always deleting them within 12 months of the event ending.</p>

<h2>Stats and analytics</h2>
<p>We may gather anonymised, aggregate statistics from the website — things like overall attendance numbers or general usage patterns. These stats never identify you personally and can't be traced back to any individual.</p>

<h2>What happens after the event</h2>
<p>Once the event is over, your publicly identifiable information is no longer in active use. We will permanently delete all of it, along with any web request logs, within 12 months of the event ending. Only anonymised aggregate statistics may be kept beyond that point.</p>

<h2>Conduct reports</h2>

<p>DeerPost.cx is an independent initiative from EMF and its organisers. However, we run within EMF and we apply the same code of conduct. If we receive a report about your behaviour under <a href="https://www.emfcamp.org/code-of-conduct">EMF's Code of Conduct</a>, we may keep the report, as well as any other observations, indefinitely. This allows us to carry out our legitimate interests of keeping the website safe for our attendees.</p>

<p>Personal information on conduct reports is only made available to the DeerPost.cx caretaker, members of the conduct team as well as the Directors of EMF.</p>

